<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Condoms at a pep rally scavenger hunt resulted in the suspension of eight 
members of the Sutter High School cheerleading squad in Marysville. The 
cheerleaders organized a scavenger hunt at a rally last week and used a list 
that included the item "protection." Two male students provided the condoms and 
turned them in with the other items. "We just don't think it's appropriate that 
they should be displayed in public in our campus," said Vice Principal Douglas 
Andreasen. "We feel it's a personal item that should be kept personal." The 
mothers of three of the cheerleaders tried to talk to school officials 
Thursday, but were told to make an appointment for a later date. Andreasen said 
the male students who provided the condoms were not punished. 
</P>
