<P>
Sheriff's detectives sought gunmen who fired several shotgun blasts into the 
Sacramento-area home of a black family after painting the house with the 
letters "KKK." Sgt. Paul Hauptman said no one was hurt in the incident in the 
south Sacramento suburb of Florin. "We just went through a living nightmare and 
we just don't understand why," homeowner Othella Jenkins said, adding that she 
had never experienced any problems in the neighborhood where she has lived 
three years. 
