<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIKE DOWNEY: REWRITING OREL'S HISTORY CAN BE CHILD'S PLAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mike Downey 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For your theoretical amusement, we now bring you: Children's Letters to Orel 
Hershiser. 
</P>
<P>
Dear Mr. Hershiser: 
</P>
<P>
I am a Little Leaguer who hopes to become a big leaguer, just like you. Please 
give me some tips. When I win 20 games some day, should I go ahead and accept 
$7.9 million in salary, or should I insist upon proper contractual language in 
case of a lockout? 
</P>
<P>
James from Baldwin Park 
</P>
