<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BUDD DENOUNCES APARTHEID ON TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South African runner Zola Budd strongly condemned apartheid in a television 
interview in Johannesburg, telling viewers that she "always hated" any form of 
racial discrimination. 
</P>
<P>
"I have always felt in my heart that I hate apartheid and always resented it," 
Budd said. "I do not believe in the superiority of one race above another based 
on the color of a person's skin." 
</P>
<P>
Budd said she did not speak out strongly against apartheid in her prime running 
days in Britain because she did not want to "get involved in the hypocrisy of 
the anti-apartheid wagon." 
</P>
<P>
Budd returned to South Africa last May after a heated controversy in Britain 
regarding her links with South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
