<HEADLINE>
<P>
CS LONG BEACH TO FACE NEVADA LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach's men's basketball team, which has a four-game winning 
streak, plays the University of Nevada Las Vegas in a Big West Conference game 
at 7:30 tonight in the Thomas and Mack Center at Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach is coming off a 66-52 victory over New Mexico State Saturday night, 
which moved the 49ers above .500 (12-11) for the first time this season. They 
also moved into a second-place tie with New Mexico State with a 9-5 record. 
</P>
<P>
In their victory over the Aggies, the 49ers were led by Tyrone Mitchell, who 
had 16 points, four assists and eight rebounds and center John Hatten, who also 
had 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach has allowed an average of 51.5 points during its winning streak, the 
49ers' longest of the season. 
</P>
<P>
Las Vegas, ranked 18th, is 18-6 overall and 11-2 in conference play and is 
coming off of a 62-60 victory over Temple Sunday. Greg Anthony and Anderson 
Hunt scored 17 points each and Stacey Augmon had 16 to lead the Rebels, who 
have a 2 1/2-game lead over the 49ers in the Big West. 
</P>
</TEXT>
