<P>
The American Iron and Steel Institute said steel imports declined 16% in 
December from a year earlier to 1.42 million tons, but imports for all of 1988 
rose 4.9% to 20.89 million tons. Despite climbing from 19.92 million tons in 
1987, imports last year represented a smaller share of the U.S. market, down to 
20.3% from 20.9%. December's imports represented 18.4% of the market, down from 
19.7% in December, 1987, when 1.69 million tons of steel entered the country. 
The market penetration in November, 1988, was 19.7%, or 1.85 million tons. 
