<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and international 
news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Production has begun on the first prime-time animated series in more than a 
decade. NBC's "Hound Town," a half-hour comedy set in a typical American 
suburb, "concerns the lives that dogs have of which humans are unaware," 
according to director Ralph Bakshi, who added: "The dogs have their own views 
of humans and ultimately turn out to be more civilized than we are." The series 
is tentatively scheduled for a Friday night time slot. 
</P>
