<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAILING; 
</P>
<P>
150 BOATS COMPETE IN SCYA REGATTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite adverse weather conditions, more than 150 boats competed in 14 races in 
the Southern California Yachting Assn.'s annual Mid-Winter Regatta Saturday and 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
In Newport Beach, the Balboa Yacht Club sponsored three classes in three 
weekend races, which drew 32 boats. 
</P>
<P>
Among the winners were: 
</P>
<P>
 -- Hare, skippered by Greg Pearce from the Newport Harbor Yacht Club, in the 
soling class. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Shy, skippered by Don Bever from the Newport Harbor Yacht Club, in the 
Etchells -- 22 Class. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Skidoo, skippered by Paul Sharp of the Bahia Corinthian Yacht Club, in the 
PHRF Class A. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Forzado, skippered by Gedfrey Phillips of the Balboa Yacht Club, in Class 
B. 
</P>
<P>
The Dana Point Yacht Club's competition drew 32 entries. 
</P>
<P>
Among the winners were: 
</P>
<P>
 -- Windward, skippered by Mike Luna of the Voyagers Yacht Club in Newport 
Beach, in the Nonspinaker. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Quit Cannon, skippered by Lance McCabe of the Dana Point Yacht Club, in the 
PHRF Class A. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Thunder Box, skippered by Dick Amtowe of the Dana Point Yacht Club, in 
Class B. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Half Fast, skippered by Tony Haines of the American Legion Yacht Club in 
Newport Beach, in Class C. 
</P>
<P>
Races were also held at the Newport Harbor, Lido Isle and Bahia Corinthian 
yacht clubs. 
</P>
